# API rules for relations · pocketbase/pocketbase · Discussion #5604
created: 2024-10-05, last updated: 2026-04-16, [Read more](https://github.com/pocketbase/pocketbase/discussions/5604)

2. `group_members` create:
```
@request.auth.id != "" &&
// prevent assigning themself as a member because the Create API rule runs AFTER dry submit of the record
@request.data.member != @request.auth.id &&
@collection.group_members.member ?= @request.auth.id &&
@collection.group_members.group ?= @request.data.group &&
@collection.group_members.role ?= "admin"
```
...
So the overall rule would read like that:
- `group.group_members_via_group.member ?= @request.auth.id` = there must be at least one group’s member with the user id
- `group.group_members_via_group.status ?!= "invited"` = and none of those ⬆️ group members have the invited status

# Complicated API rule · pocketbase pocketbase · Discussion #3805
created: 2023-11-21, last updated: 2026-04-16, [Read more](https://github.com/pocketbase/pocketbase/discussions/3805)

And then the `users` List API rule could look something like:
```
@request.auth.id != "" &&
@collection.courseRegistrations.user ?= @request.auth.id &&
@collection.courseRegistrationsView.user ?= id
@collection.courseRegistrations.courseGroup ?= @collection.courseRegistrationsView.courseGroup
```
...
*edit: updated to use `?=` because otherwise it will require every joined record to match with the condition.*
...
Just an example how the above rule could look if we decide to use `@collection.someCollection:someAlias.*` syntax with the next release:
```
@request.auth.id != "" &&
@collection.courseRegistrations.user ?= id &&
@collection.courseRegistrations:auth.user ?= @request.auth.id &&
@collection.courseRegistrations.courseGroup ?= @collection.courseRegistrations:auth.courseGroup
```

